column1: ***PLEASE NOTE: Level 3 Communications and Global Crossing have merged as of October 4, 2011
However, at this time all offers from the respective companies remain separate. Attached offer is from
Level 3 only. Existing Global Crossing rates remain unaffected at this time.
We value and appreciate your business. Please call your Account Executive or the International Marketing Manager
if you have any questions regarding this rate notification.
For all traffic terminating in the 48 contiguous United States over the Level 3 Communications Global Switching Platforms ("GSPs") as well as the International Soft
Switches (ISS): 1) all NPA-555 calls seeking directory assistance/information will be billed at $0.95 per call; and 2) if more than 20% of such traffic during any billing period
is terminated in local exchange areas not serviced by a Regional Bell Operating Company (RBOC), GTE/Verizon, or a wireless provider, an additional charge of $0.04 per
minute will be added to all traffic in excess of such 20% threshold (billed as an adjustment to the original invoice for the relevant billing period). This service is intended
for International-originated USA traffic only. As such Intrastate calls will be assessed a surcharge of .15 for any amount above 5% of total US traffic sent.
Please note that all dates are effective at 12:01 AM Greenwich Mean Time (GMT) of the listed Effective date.
